<br>
Stolen from Bristlebane's Personal Diary<br>
<br>
  Took notice of a young Wallet Inspection Technician today.  His prayers have been loyal and true... he's been passing out shade silk robes to Dark Elf warriors and shadowknights and telling them to be mages, advertising rediculus items on market, and trying to sell a manastone.  Also noticed him running about looking for group as an iksar ranger.  However, it pains me to see that he is unable to mascarade as a gnomish druid.  He has called to me, wishing that I may bless him with the ability to become such a being.  That, and to turn into a bixie.  And to make a pet that will talk back to him so he can pretend he's a caster who just learned to make their pet and it won't obey.  Not a bad idea.  Mental note, summon bixie druid that argues with it's pet.  Hmm, speaking of which, I bet it would be funny if during a Kael raid I made all of Resolution's Mod Rods disappear and blamed it on that Bako character... hmm... well anyway where was I?  Ah yes.  The Alternative Materials Aquisisions Specialist.  Really must work on him getting gnome powers.  But how...<br>
  Ah yes!  I know it!  I shall force Rollen to give this young one such a mask, and then he shall spread pranks and mischeif all over the land!  He can whack a decaying skeleton with a shade silk robe on and be a gnomish necromancer!  Whack a dog, start casting strength buffs, and be a gnomish shaman!  Yes... and if Rollen does not give it to him, I shall rain great pranks down upon him!  I shall cause all his mod rods to cast gravity flux!  I shall send a rampaging horde of snow bunnies to gnaw him into oblivion!  I shall cause the cursed in Ssra to drop nothing but copies of Improved Invisibility to Undead!  I shall turn his entire guild PvP during AoE grouping!  That ought to show him for killing my puppet in my plain, which I so cleverly disguised as the real me!  Muhahahaha...<br>
<br>
<br>
Jarkell Ravensteel<br>
